Description: Lower body and foot sherd of East Greek pottery cup; interior reserved; exterior glazed black (fired partly red) on body and ring foot; reserved on underside; traces of dipinto inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 660)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.136)
